heterogeneity of AD (with diverse genetic backgrounds, brain region 
vulnerability, and protein misfolding profiles)12, understanding how 
GLP-1RAs perform across disease subtypes will be essential. In addi-
tion, it would be exciting to explore whether combining GLP-1RAs with 
emerging anti-amyloid therapies (such as lecanemab or donanemab) 
could yield synergistic effects. Finally, given the shared metabolic 
deficits across many neurodegenerative diseases13, GLP-1RAs also hold 
great promise to be repurposed for conditions such as Parkinson’s 
disease or frontotemporal dementia.
